# apps/mobile — Mobile (Expo + React Native)

## Stack

- **Expo SDK** with **expo-router** (file-based routing)
- **React Native** with **React 19**
- **NativeWind** — Tailwind for React Native
- **TypeScript** strict mode

## Layout

```
apps/mobile/
├── app.json               # Expo config
├── src/
│   ├── app/               # expo-router file-based routes
│   ├── components/        # shared UI
│   ├── features/          # feature code (created by `feature` generator)
│   └── lib/
├── assets/
└── package.json
```

## Run / Test / Build

```sh
pnpm --filter @<%= projectName %>/mobile dev               # expo start
pnpm --filter @<%= projectName %>/mobile test             # vitest run
pnpm --filter @<%= projectName %>/mobile build:ios        # eas build --platform ios
pnpm --filter @<%= projectName %>/mobile build:android    # eas build --platform android
```

For native builds you need an Expo account and EAS CLI configured.

## Conventions

- **Routes are file-based** under `src/app/` via expo-router (`_layout.tsx`, `index.tsx`, `[param].tsx`).
- **Components**: PascalCase, default export, no `any` props.
- **Styling**: NativeWind className utilities — keep platform-specific overrides in `style` props, not separate files.
- **No barrel files** inside `src/`.

## Adding a new feature

```sh
pnpm nx generate @<%= projectName %>/project-plugin:feature --name <name> --apps mobile
```
